{White's last move was 16.Bb3-c4. His main idea was to fight against the
threat of 16...Ba6 followed by a5-a4. Do you agree with that?} 16... Qa4 {
This strong move shatters White's stability on light squares.} 17. Bd3 Nxd3 18.
Qxd3 Ba6 19. Qd2 f6 20. Be3 f5 {There is no satisfactory way of defending e4
so White has to give up the centre.} 21. exf5 gxf5 22. f4 {A desperate move
making things only worse.} Rae8 $17 {Black's pressure along the e-file soon
got him an exchange.} *

