{By centralizing his queen, White is attacking the knight. How should Black
proceed here?} 1... b5 $1 {The is the right reaction. It is very important to
keep the control over the c4-square. Weaker is 15...Nd6 16.c4 b6 17.Be3 when
White has the initiative.} 2. Qb1 Qd7 3. Rd1 Bf8 $1 {This exchange leaves
White with a potentially bad bishop, while the knight remains the dominating
minor piece.} 4. Bxf8 Rxf8 5. O-O c5 {With obvious advantage for Black} *

