{White has just met the move 24...g3 by means of 25.h3. Which is the best way
to proceed with the attack?} 25... Nf7 $1 {The knight was not doing much on d6
anymore. Black plans ...Qh4 followed by ...Ng5 and ...Bxh3.} (25... Qh4 $1 {
followed by ...Nf7 would have been the same}) (25... Bxh3 $6 26. gxh3 g2 27.
Qxg2 $1 (27. Rf2 $6 Qg3 {Threatening ...Qh2!+} 28. Rxg2 Qxe1+ 29. Kh2 Rxg2+ 30.
Kxg2 Kf7 $17) 27... Qf6 28. Kh2 Rxg2+ 29. Rxg2 {The attack came to an end and
White has enough compensation for the queen.}) 26. a5 Qh4 27. axb6 Ng5 28. b7
Bxb7 29. Ba5 Bc8 30. Re1 Bxh3 31. Kf1 (31. gxh3 Nxh3+ 32. Kf1 Nf2 {followed by
...g3-g2 wins}) 31... Bd7 $1 *

