{White plans Qb1 followed by Rc1 with string queenside pressure and an
absolutely safe king. Can you find a way of putting the pawns into motion?} 
1... Rfb8 $1 {Since things are calm on the kingside Black affords
concentrating his rooks on the queenside for the sake of reaching ...b6-b5.} 2.
Qb1 b5 3. axb5 axb5 4. Nxb5 Bxb5 5. Bxb5 c4 6. Rb2 Qb7 {would have offered
excellent compensation for the pawn.} *

